why do countries try to protect their own firms from the world market? There are a few reasons why countries might try to protect their firms from the world market. One reason is that the country might want to ensure that its firms are able to compete in the global market. Another reason is that the country might want to protect its firms from foreign competition in order to promote domestic industry. Finally, the country might want to protect its firms from the negative effects of globalization, such as job losses or the decline of domestic industries.

moscow treaty on strategic offensive reductions The Moscow Treaty on Strategic Offensive Reductions (SORT) was a treaty between the United States of America and the Russian Federation on the Reduction and Limitation of Strategic Offensive Arms. The treaty was signed on May 24, 2002, in Moscow, and took effect on June 1, 2003.
